      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ahmad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Abdul Rahman Bin Al Armany, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, from his<sup>asws</sup> father<sup>asws</sup>, from Ali<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one in <span class=\"iTxt\">Ihraam</span> can kill whatever he fears upon himself’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "10. Ahmad has narrated from Ali ibn al-Hakam from ‘Abd al-Rahman al-‘Arzamiy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘One in the state of Ihram can kill anything whereby one fears for his life.’” "
        ]
